Text.Value: Easy - now I'm going to kill you.
You're free, so... what do you want to happen?
We're creatures of the shadows. I'm sure you know that feeling well.
We're still creatures of the shadows. Nothing can change that.
Are you going to kill us like you killed the others?
Why not embrace the dark? You could find a home in the Underdark.
I do, so why not embrace it? You could make a true home in the Underdark.
Where is he? What have you done?
You can try, but I'm not some helpless wretch in a cage. I'm going to make you bleed.
Easy to say, but it's not like we can just march out into the city.
We're not, but thank you all the same. You didn't have to do any of this.
What - what happens now?
You did it. You destroyed him.
I... I don't know. We can't stay here, but can't just march out into city either.
I'm sure I can resist. I've survived this long on vermin, after all.
We could do worse. We could do well, even.
Maybe I should kill you after all...
Why not start over in the Underdark?
You said I was free! You said I could go!
Thank you for this chance. For our freedom.
True, we'd never have to fear the sun. Never have to fear vampire hunters.
That depends. Are you going to start feeding on people?
No, you're free to go.
We can't stay here, though. Baldur's Gate will always have Cazador's shadow hanging over it.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: 'his' referring to Cazador, his now-dead abusive master
EditorData.NodeContext: 'his' referring to Cazador, his now-dead abusive master

Text.Value: I've never seen him bleed before. I didn't know it was possible.
We'll find somewhere quiet and consider our options. Good luck up there.
Indeed I am.
Do what you like, you're not my problem.

Synopsis: Dialog with a spawn after Cazador is defeated, but spawn is not killed / left yet.
